Article.Abstract: Little is known regarding the participation of CD4+ CD25+ regulatory T cells (Treg) in TCD8+ responses. In this study, we show that Treg depletion via treatment with anti-CD25 mAb (PC61) significantly enhances TCD8+ responses to influenza A virus, vaccinia virus, and SV40-transformed cells induced by either direct priming or cross-priming. PC61 did not enhance TCD8+ responses in CD4-deficient mice, providing the initial demonstration that PC61 acts on a subset of TCD4+, and not on other cells that express either CD25 or a fortuitously cross-reactive Ag. We further show that Treg selectively suppress responses to the most immunodominant TCD8+ determinants in the three systems examined. Therefore, Treg influence TCD8 immunodominance hierarchies by moderating disparities in responses to different determinants.
Article.ArticleTitle: Regulatory T cells suppress CD8+ T cell responses induced by direct priming and cross-priming and moderate immunodominance disparities.

FirstInVivoProcess.DoseSchedule: One dose of 2x10<sup>7</sup> SV40-transformed C57SV cells.

Immunization.ImmunizationComments: 4 days prior to priming, mice were given i.p. 500 micrograms of anti-CD25 mAb PC61 while control mice were given a mock PBS injection. .

AssayInformation.AssayComments: The CD8+ response against this epitope, subdominant only to epitope IV on the same source protein, is enhanced in spleen lymphocytes of mice depleted of regulatory T cells by anti-CD25 Ab injection prior to immunization with SV-40-transformed cells. This effect is seen both with syngeneic and allogeneic (in this case also in peritoneal lymphocytes) transformed cells as the immunogen. By contrast, no enhancement is seen upon immunization with a recombinant vaccinia virus encoding the source protein.

FirstInVivoProcess.DoseSchedule: One dose of 2x10<sup>7</sup> SV40-transformed C57SV cells.

Immunization.ImmunizationComments: 4 days prior to priming, mice were given i.p. 500 micrograms of anti-CD25 mAb PC61 while control mice were given a mock PBS injection. .

AssayInformation.AssayComments: CD8+ mediated lysis of peptide pulsed EL-4 cells is enhanced in mice depleted of regulatory T cells by anti-CD25 Ab injection prior to immunization with SV40-transformed cells. This effect is also seen in an in vivo cytotoxicity assay.

FirstInVivoProcess.DoseSchedule: One dose of 2x10<sup>7</sup> SV40-transformed C57SV cells.

Immunization.ImmunizationComments: 4 days prior to priming, mice were given i.p. 500 micrograms of anti-CD25 mAb PC61 while control mice were given a mock PBS injection. .

AssayInformation.AssayComments: CD8+ response against this immunodominant epitope is enhanced both in spleen and peritoneal lymphocytes of mice depleted of regulatory T cells by anti-CD25 Ab injection prior to immunization with SV40-transformed cells. This effect is also seen when allogeneic transformed cells or recombinant vaccinia virus encoding T-antigen or epitope minigene are used as immunogens, and is dependent on the CD25+ subset of CD4+ lymphocytes (and not on other possible CD25+ cells). Responses against epitopes of lower dominance hierarchy on T-antigen and also of other viruses are less enhanced by CD25 depletion, implying that the overall effect of regulatory T cells is to moderate immunodominance disparities by suppressing responses to immunodominant epitopes.
